			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The NES PPU fetches sprite patterns during horizontal blanking. Based on what I know about the Super NES's background fetch pattern, as well as the difference between the 32 sprite and 34 sliver limits, it's overwhelmingly likely that the Super NES PPU does likewise. So you won't get any sprites on the line after the horizontal blanking period in which you forced blanking.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
